narratives.question_text: How would you summarize ECON 110 05 for a fellow student? Would you recommend ECON 110 05 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: I would cautiously recommend FREN 170 to a student who is eager to put in a lot of work and do a lot of reading. The readings are hard and long, but some of them are quite fascinating and Mme Girard provides insightful commentary.
This is a good class, but it turned into more of a lecture than a seminar. The reading list makes it worth it.

I would definitely recommend this course to anyone interested in reading the classic authors of French literature. It's going to be difficult to understand everything, but Mme Girard does a very good job of helping you progress in your french reading comprehension. My main hesitation with it was that it was at 9:00 AM, but it was worth waking up early for.
